entries.title: U.S. and China lay out competing security visions for Asia-Pacific
entries.description: Speeches by Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin and Chinese counterpart Dong Jun at the Shangri-La Dialogue heavily referenced Taiwan and underscored growing U.S.-China tensions.

entries.title: Mexico is choosing a new president. Here’s why the election is historic.
entries.description: Voters on Sunday are expected to elect Mexico’s first female president.

entries.title: Chinese probe lands on ‘dark’ side of the moon to collect rare samples
entries.description: The mission could be the first to retrieve samples from the far side of the moon, as a space rivalry between the United States and China heats up.

entries.title: Biden announced a cease-fire plan for the war in Gaza. Here’s what to know.
entries.description: The three-phase plan includes the release of remaining hostages, Israeli military withdrawal from Gaza, a surge in aid and a path to a permanent end to hostilities.

entries.title: Israeli reservists fight in Gaza but question what comes after the war
entries.description: There’s little consensus in Israel on how to manage Gaza after the war. It’s a question that is on the minds of some reservists who are essential to the fight.

entries.title: Basic training in Ukraine is barely covering the basics, commanders say
entries.description: Ukrainian commanders in the field say they are bracing for most of the new troops under a new conscription law to arrive with poor training.

entries.title: Biden team hails ‘lightning speed’ call on strikes in Russia. Meanwhile, Kharkiv burned.
entries.description: Washington finally allowed Kyiv to strike limited targets inside Russia. But it might be too little, too late.

entries.title: Serial killer Robert Pickton dies 22 years after a gruesome discovery
entries.description: Pickton, 74, was convicted of murdering six women in British Columbia, though authorities think he may have killed dozens more.

entries.title: Pressure builds on Netanyahu to advance Gaza cease-fire deal
entries.description: Thousands of people rallied in Tel Aviv in support of a cease-fire proposal outlined by President Biden.

entries.title: A former Israeli hostage recalls the brutality of Hamas captivity
entries.description: Moran Stella Yanai was abducted on Oct. 7 and was sure that her life “would end,” she said.

entries.title: Mexico’s presidential election: Meet the candidates
entries.description: The vote Sunday pits a female Jewish engineer against an Indigenous female tech entrepreneur and a millennial congressman.

entries.title: It’s Pride Month: How LGBTQ+ rights changed around the world this past year
entries.description: While more bills targeting LGBTQ+ rights were introduced in U.S. state legislatures, other countries expanded marriage rights for same-sex couples.

entries.title: What to know about India’s election, the world’s biggest democratic event
entries.description: After 47 days of elections, Indians will get a new Parliament that the Bharatiya Janata Party is still expected to dominate.

entries.title: Israeli troops withdraw from Gaza’s Jabalya, leaving devastation
entries.description: Israeli forces have “completed their mission” in Gaza’s Jabalya refugee camp, the military said, months after declaring victory there in a previous operation.

entries.title: Biden announces new cease-fire plan for Gaza
entries.description: The Israeli deal would see the release of hostages, a flood of humanitarian aid and a multi-stage process for a permanent cessation of violence and full IDF withdrawal.

entries.title: Mapping Israel’s expanding battle for Rafah, a test of U.S. red lines
entries.description: Israel’s military confirmed it is operating in central Rafah. Videos and satellite imagery show forces pushing into populated areas, razing scores of buildings.

entries.title: Anti-Islam activist among six wounded in stabbing in Germany
entries.description: The stabbing took place during a far-right event in Mannheim, Germany, to “educate about political Islam.”

entries.title: Blinken opens the door to attacks with U.S. weapons deeper inside Russia
entries.description: After President Biden said that Ukraine could use donated U.S. weapons for limited strikes on targets in Russia, Berlin quickly followed suit.

entries.title: As Indian voting wraps up, reports of electoral irregularities mount
entries.description: Opponents of the ruling Bharatiya Janata Party have accused its supporters of suppressing turnout and intimidating candidates. The BJP denies the allegations.

entries.title: South Africa’s ruling ANC on track to lose majority for the first time
entries.description: The election’s real winner, in third place with nearly 12 percent of the vote, was the new MK Party of former president Jacob Zuma, once an ANC stalwart.

entries.title: Amid tension, U.S. and China defense chiefs hold first meeting in two years
entries.description: Defense Secretary Lloyd J. Austin met his Chinese counterpart Dong Jun in Singapore to try to prevent miscommunication in the South China Sea and around Taiwan from spiraling into a crisis.

entries.title: Ukraine can use U.S. weapons for limited strikes in Russia, Biden says
entries.description: The dramatic shift in U.S. policy comes after Russia’s assault on the city of Kharkiv and a chorus of pressure from European allies.

entries.title: Joint U.S.-British attack kills at least 16 in Yemen; Houthis claim attack on carrier
entries.description: British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak said the strikes overnight Thursday were taken in self-defense and “to prevent further attacks on international shipping.”

entries.title: A TikToker interviewed ‘Elvis’ director Baz Luhrmann without realizing it
entries.description: TikToker Georgia Godworth says she had no idea she was talking to the world-famous director Baz Luhrmann while doing street interviews in Newtown, Sydney.

entries.title: Deaths mount and water rationed as India faces record heat
entries.description: Reports of heat-related illnesses and deaths have surged across the country as daytime highs continue to hover around 120 degrees and nights remain over 90.
